hl — Run aarch64-linux ELF binaries on macOS Apple Silicon
==========================================================

Quick Start
-----------

  No installation required.  Run directly from this directory:

    ./hl <elf-binary>
    ./hl --verbose ./my-static-program arg1 arg2

Install
-------

  Optional system-wide installation (default: /usr/local):

    ./configure
    sudo make install

  Custom prefix:

    ./configure --prefix=$HOME/.local
    make install

  Remove:

    sudo make uninstall

Dynamic Linking
---------------

  For dynamically-linked aarch64-linux ELF binaries, supply a musl
  sysroot containing the dynamic linker and shared libraries:

    ./hl --sysroot /path/to/musl-sysroot ./my-dynamic-program

Man Page
--------

  Before installation:    man ./hl.1
  After installation:     man hl

  hl --help also displays the man page automatically.

Requirements
------------

  - Apple Silicon Mac (arm64)
  - macOS 13 (Ventura) or later
  - Hypervisor entitlement is embedded in the signed binary

